We creating portfolio website that looks like mind map like Miro.

Pages:
All pages looks like connected blocks with links from a left or right side and stored on a Pages page in Figma.
with the same reusable menu component. Pages may be navigated only via links in menu. User may not zoom in or out.

All pages in figma is a part of a map group. Map group is a visual representation of how pages actually attached.

Architecture:
Single-page app with one map canvas. All route cards exist in the same DOM. History API routes: /, /about, /blog, /cases, /contacts.

Loading:
For showcasing home screen we need to load homepage, all lines to the other blocks and their navigation menus. When user navigates to one of the blocks - we start to load page content.

Content:
Page content will be provided later in Figma. Implementation uses Figma MCP as source of truth for structure, copy, and assets when ready. All route cards ship as blank shells (menu + empty content area) until Figma content is added.

Pages folder (p:*) may exist for future use but is not the content source of truth for implementation.

Transitions:
- Camera pans the map canvas to center the active card (ease-in-out, 650ms).
- Departing card scales to 95% during navigation; arriving card scales from 95% to 100%.
- Connector lines are drawn dynamically in code between Dot icons (not static SVG assets).
- Browser Back/Forward must work via popstate.

